## Quick start (GenLayer Studio)

1. Deploy `contract/governance_simulator.py` to GenLayer Studionet.
2. Copy the deployed contract address into `frontend/index.html` (`CONTRACT_ADDRESS` constant).
3. Deploy this repository to Vercel as a static site with **Root Directory
   set to the repository root** (not `frontend/`). The frontend fetches
   `../demo/proposals.json` at runtime for its example-proposal chips, so
   `demo/` needs to be served alongside `frontend/` — deploying only the
   `frontend` subfolder will 404 on that fetch (it falls back to two
   hardcoded chips in that case, so the page still works, just with fewer
   examples).
4. Open `<your-deployment>/frontend/index.html`, paste a governance
   proposal, submit — the contract returns a structured multi-scenario
   simulation report.

## Demo

See `demo/proposals.json` for example proposals (treasury, quorum, validator
rewards, fees, emission) and `demo/demo.py` to run them all against a deployed
contract in one command.

